                  processed:
                    '<h3>For mental health care appointments</h3>\n\n<p>Call the behavioral health call center.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Phone: </strong>412-360-6600</p>\n\n<h3>For drug or alcohol evaluation and treatment appointments</h3>\n\n<p>Call the Center for Treatment of Addictive Disorders (CTAD).</p>\n\n<p><strong>Phone: </strong>412-360-6092</p>\n\n<h3>For walk-in mental health care</h3>\n\n<p>If you need help right away, or if you have a referral from another VA provider, one of our counselors will see you the same day. Same-day mental health and psychiatric help is available for both new and established patients.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Available at University Drive</strong></p>\n\n<p class="va-address-block"><strong>Outpatient Behavioral Clinic</strong><br />\nBuilding 29<br />\nWaiting Room 1<br /><a data-entity-substitution="canonical" data-entity-type="node" data-entity-uuid="71ffee52-a47f-4909-ad7e-21ece5728be3" href="/pittsburgh-health-care/university-drive-campus-map" title="University Drive campus map">Map of University Drive campus</a><br /><strong>Phone: </strong>412-360-6600</p>\n\n<p><strong>Hours: </strong>Monday – Friday, 8:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. ET</p>\n\n<h3>For walk-in drug or alcohol evaluation and treatment</h3>\n\n<p>Same-day help is available through CTAD at the Outpatient Behavioral Clinic.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Available at University Drive</strong></p>\n\n<p class="va-address-block"><strong>Outpatient Behavioral Clinic</strong><br />\nBuilding 29<br />\nWaiting Room 3<br /><a data-entity-substitution="canonical" data-entity-type="node" data-entity-uuid="71ffee52-a47f-4909-ad7e-21ece5728be3" href="/pittsburgh-health-care/university-drive-campus-map" title="University Drive campus map">Map of University Drive campus</a><br /><strong>Phone: </strong>412-360-6092</p>\n\n<h3>Specialty care appointments</h3>\n\n<p>If you already have a primary care provider at VA Pittsburgh health care, you can make a direct appointment for the specialty services listed here. You don\'t need to get a referral or see your primary care provider first.</p>\n\n<p>For specialty care services not listed here, please contact your primary care provider for a referral.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Amputee clinic </strong><br />\n412-822-3017<br />\n    <br /><strong>Audiology (hearing)</strong><br />\n412-360-6400<br /><strong>    <br />\nMammograms</strong><br />\n412-360-3306<br />\n    <br /><strong>MOVE (weight loss and healthy living)</strong><br />\n412-822-3114<br />\n    <br /><strong>Nutrition services </strong><br />\n412-822-3000<br />\n    <br /><strong>Optometry (eye care)</strong> <br />\n412-360-6700<br />\n    <br /><strong>Podiatry (foot and ankle care) </strong><br />\n412-822-3000<br />\n    <br /><strong>Wheelchair and power seating clinic </strong><br />\n412-822-2180</p>',
