                  processed:
                    '<h3>Phone refills (automated refill line)</h3>\n\n<p>412-822-3140<br />\n866-482-7488, select 1 (toll free from outside the Pittsburgh area)</p>\n\n<h3>Mail refills</h3>\n\n<p>Mail back the refill request form that comes with your prescription to the provided address.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Please don’t drop off the form at the pharmacy when you pick up your new prescription. We can’t process refill requests on the same day that new prescriptions are picked up.</p>\n\n<h2>Pick up new prescriptions</h2>\n\n<p>You can pick up new prescription orders at one of our VA Pittsburgh health care pharmacies.</p>\n\n<p>We ask that you don\'t try to refill prescriptions in person, so our pharmacists can focus on providing care to Veterans with urgent needs and new prescriptions. Refills are only available online, by phone or mail.</p>\n\n<h3>University Drive campus</h3>\n\n<p class="va-address-block">Main Hospital<br />\nBuilding 1<br />\nPittsburgh, PA 15240-1003<br /><a data-entity-substitution="canonical" data-entity-type="node" data-entity-uuid="71ffee52-a47f-4909-ad7e-21ece5728be3" href="/pittsburgh-health-care/university-drive-campus-map" title="University Drive campus map">Map of University Drive campus</a><br /><strong>Hours:</strong><br />\nMon – Fri, 7:30 a.m. to 9:00 p.m. ET<br />\nSat, Sun, and holidays, 7:30 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. ET</p>\n\n<h3>Heinz campus</h3>\n\n<p class="va-address-block">1010 Delafield Road<br />\nBuilding 71<br />\nFirst Floor<br />\nPittsburgh, PA 15215<br /><a data-entity-substitution="canonical" data-entity-type="node" data-entity-uuid="a2d3391d-7196-4a3e-bdf5-a71a7b214195" href="/pittsburgh-health-care/hj-heinz-iii-campus-map" title="H.J. Heinz III campus map">Map of the Heinz campus</a><br /><strong>Hours: </strong>Mon – Fri, 8:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. ET</p>\n\n<h2>Contact us with questions about your prescriptions</h2>\n\n<h3>Pharmacy support</h3>\n\n<p><strong>Phone:</strong> 866-400-1242<br /><strong>Hours: </strong>Mon – Fri, 8:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. ET</p>\n\n<h2>Safely dispose of your medicine</h2>\n\n<p>Drop off your expired or unwanted medicine at a MedSafe box. Disposing of your medicines safely can help protect other people as well as the environment.</p>\n\n<p>You can find the large blue MedSafe boxes at:</p>\n\n<ul><li>University Drive campus, Building 1</li>\n\t<li>Heinz campus, Building 51, Community Living Center</li>\n</ul>',
