              entity: {
                entityType: 'paragraph',
                entityBundle: 'wysiwyg',
                fieldWysiwyg: {
                  processed:
                    '<h3>Information for research professionals</h3>\n\n<p>Welcome to the VA Pittsburgh Healthcare System\'s Research Office website for Research Professionals. This site is dedicated to individuals who are interested in conducting research at VAPHS, research staff, and those serving on our research committees. Here you can find information related to the various types of research we conduct, including forms, standard operating procedures and checklists.</p>\n\n<h3>VA Pittsburgh Research Annual Report</h3>\n\n<p>Please download the 2019 VA Pittsburgh Research Annual Report to learn more about the most recent research programs and findings.</p>\n\n<div data-embed-button="file" data-entity-embed-display="file:file_default" data-entity-embed-display-settings="1 2019 VA Pittsburgh Research Annual Report" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="a07ea6ba-b705-4b24-8d11-13b79b98fb5e" data-langcode="en" class="embedded-entity">\n<span class="file file--mime-application-pdf file--application-pdf"> <a href="https://prod.cms.va.gov/sites/default/files/2020-09/ResearchAR2019_final_2.10.20.pdf" type="application/pdf; length=1972021" title="ResearchAR2019_final_2.10.20.pdf">2019 VA Pittsburgh Research Annual Report</a></span>\n</div>\n<h3>Notifications of research publications and publicity</h3>\n\n<p>If you are a VAPHS Investigator, remember that you are required to notify the VAPHS Research Office upon receipt of initial notice of all accepted publications, and initial notice of anticipated/scheduled presentations, media/interviews, or other professional activities related to VA research to ensure that the contributions of the Department of Veteran Affairs (VA) are appropriately acknowledged and publicly disclosed.<br /><br />\nVAPHS Investigators should use the <a href="http://vaww.w2k8.internet.staging.va.gov/PITTSBURGH/Research/docs/Notification-Accepted-Publication-Presentation8-2017.pdf">VAPHS Research Publicity Form</a> to notify the Research Office and fulfill this requirement.<br /><br />\nA guidance has been created with information and instructions related to sending notifications, please  <a href="http://vhapthsqlirb.v04.med.va.gov/VAIRBProd/Doc/0/2PC77KQ0LU34P5BVLN97D4779F/Guidance%20on%20Notification%20of%20Publications%20and%20Research%20Publicity%20v1.1.pdf">review this guidance document</a> and submit all notifications of research publicity forms to <a href="mailto:VHAPTHResearchPublicity@va.gov">VHAPTHResearchPublicity@va.gov</a>.</p>',
                },
                entityId: '12973',
              },
