                '<p>Alan Petrazzi is Acting Deputy Director of VA Pittsburgh Healthcare System (VAPHS). As acting deputy director, he oversees many of VAPHS’ operational roles, including facilities management and police. Mr. Petrazzi began his VA career in 2007 as director of VAPHS’ physical rehabilitation services. He has served as VAPHS assistant director, VAPHS acting associate director, operations manager for primary care, and interim director of VA Butler Healthcare. Mr. Petrazzi holds master’s degrees in physical therapy and public management. He is a 2014 graduate of the Healthcare Leadership Development Program and a fellow of the American College of Healthcare Executives (ACHE).</p>',
